  <h2>Description</h2>
  <p>Stocking your freezer with crispy, cooked chicken patties is a great way to avoid takeout. You can turn those
    patties into a fast-food sandwich dupe with special sauce or a kind of shortcut tonkatsu. Or you can make one of my
    family's favorites: lazy chicken parmesan.</p>
  <p>I actually love making the real thing from scratch, but pounding cutlets, setting up a breading station, and frying
    each piece isn't a weeknight task. Instead, with just three ingredients—breaded chicken patties, a jar of marinara
    sauce, and some shredded mozzarella cheese—we can enjoy the comfort of chicken parmesan in under 30 minutes and with
    fewer dishes.</p>

  <h3>Ingredients</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>1 (24-ounce) bag frozen Just Bare Lightly Breaded Chicken Breast Fillets</li>
    <li>1 (12.3-ounce) jar Rao’s Pizza Sauce</li>
    <li>1 (8-ounce) bag Kraft shredded mozzarella cheese</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Steps</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>Preheat the oven according to the back-of-the-bag directions; for Just Bare Lightly Breaded Chicken Breast
        Fillets, this is 400°F. You can line a baking sheet with foil and coat it with nonstick spray for even easier
        cleanup. Arrange the chicken breast fillets on the baking sheet and cook until crispy, about 22 to 24 minutes.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Carefully remove the pan from the oven and spoon about 1/4 cup of the pizza sauce onto each breast filet. You
        can use as little or as much as you like. Sprinkle each breast with about 1/3 cup of the mozzarella.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Return the pan to the hot oven and cook until the cheese is melted and just beginning to brown, for 3 to 5
        minutes more. Serve the chicken parmesan hot with sides of your choice. </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
